      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Money Hustle: Gore's Opportunity</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jim Chamberlain letter supports Sen Joseph I Lieberman's criticism of Hollywood for marketing 'death and degradation to our children'</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Moguls Rattled by Gore's Choice of Critic of Entertainment Industry'' (news article, Aug. 11):</p>
        <p>Either Senator Joseph I. Lieberman's criticism of Hollywood for marketing ''death and degradation to our children'' is on target or it is not. Either repeated exposure of children to violent imagery as entertainment desensitizes children to violence, or it does not.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Moguls Rattled by Gore's Choice of Critic of Entertainment Industry'' (news article, Aug. 11):</p>
        <p>Either Senator Joseph I. Lieberman's criticism of Hollywood for marketing ''death and degradation to our children'' is on target or it is not. Either repeated exposure of children to violent imagery as entertainment desensitizes children to violence, or it does not.</p>
        <p>You quote the actor Warren Beatty as saying, ''I don't think it's possible to attribute the high level of mayhem in this country to movies and music.'' It troubles me that Mr. Beatty (and others in the entertainment industry) seem to think that nothing more needs to be said about the subject.</p>
        <p>JIM CHAMBERLAIN  Shorewood, Wis., Aug. 11, 2000</p>
      </block>
